  "category": "Security",
  "category_int": 3,
  "feature_notes": "We would like to modify Chromium's behavior before the spec PR lands, because:\n\n* We can improve security for users immediately, without violating the current spec.\n* We can make Chromium's SAA implementation more aligned with existing web platform behavior immediately, without violating the current spec.\n* Other browser vendors are unlikely to modify their own browsers' behavior to be more restrictive here until they also support an alternative, namely https://chromestatus.com/feature/6146353156849664. Implementing and shipping that would take time, during which Chromium users would be unnecessarily vulnerable and adoption of the SAA would increase (meaning more breakage when we eventually did ship this behavior change).",
  "web_feature": "storage-access",
